description:
This program is part of a series on the Beatitudes of Jesus. In this episode, we will look at what Jesus meant when he taught, "Blessed are those who are persecuted." This teaching will be illustrated with the life of Dietrich Bonhoeffer, who was persecuted by the Nazi regime in Germany and became a modern-day martyr.

=== CHAPTERS ===
00:00 Intro
00:23 Adolf Hitler Assassination Attempt (Operation Valkyrie)
02:32 The Beatitudes: Blessed are the persecuted
04:40 What is Martyrdom?
05:26 Dietrich Bonhoeffer early life
08:44 Dietrich Bonhoeffer during World War 2
11:22 The Cost of Discipleship
13:29 Bonhoeffer joins the German Secret Service as a double agent
16:37 Dietrich Bonhoeffer's execution, final sermon, and legacy
17:20 Biblical and historical lessons related to the story
25:41 FREE BOOKLET
27:08 Closing Prayer
